Born 1937 [as Peter Papaloizou]. Parents separated soon afterwards, only child.
\par Mother [Ruby Ahern] had been earlier cook and housekeeper; managed two hotels for Workers Travel Association in Scotland. At start of war in London, ran cr\'e8che. With blitz, moved to Cornwall, where clerical worker; later ran tobaccon}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 ists in Torquay. Kept moving: Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375 
 went to ten different schools by age 10. Early relationship easy and loving but became uneasy in his teens, when he became academic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 
; she was a single mother and Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375  felt it was a burden to be the focus of her love. Strained relationship, thr
ough university, which he now regrets.
\par Later she became a typist and established civil servant in the Ministry of Labour.
\par Father saw only twice as a child. Once aged 10 in Brixton Library, when he felt disloyal to mother, and disliked stepmother; and at 16, in court. He gave no financial support except briefly after court order. Mother\rquote 
s older brother did give some financial support, but in hi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 s childhood money very tight. Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375  not socialised into father\rquote s Cypriot world. Greek name, but spoke no Greek; but did choose to study classical Greek at Dulwich College.
\par Early schools}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 :}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375 
 Remembers learning to read. No important influences until secondary school. Incident in Brixton primary school where attacked for identifying with side of Jews rather than Arabs. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375 
 sat 11 plus, won scholarship to Dulwich College}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 . Mother liked the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
