 manners of the pupils and pushed him educationally. At that time socialist headmaster, Gilkes, keen to encourage scholarship boys. Three influential teachers, two in English Lit, one histor
ian [Laurie Jagger, John Foster and Clive Baggley], all encouraging, positive feedback on essays. Groomed for Oxbridge scholarships, intensive preparation at lunchtime of elite group of selected stars. Tutors encouraged reading on social issues, but inocu
lated him against Communism with books chosen (Koestler, Orwell): became a social democrat Contrast with schoolmate Ken Biggs who converted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid2321746 
