\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375 
; village studies catching his imagination with vivid writing about identifiable human beings, rather than just statistics. Against elaborated polysyllabic theory. Turned off by Parsons.
\par Problem of checking reliability of psychological interpretations. Qua
litative work has to be based on inferential judgements. Against disciplinary imperialisms, anthropology one of many social sciences. Believes in mixed methods, statistics valuable. Later worked with demographer [Christopher Langford] on property transfer
s and marriage market in Cyprus.
\par But after Harvard decided to go for film for next five years. Interested in social realist directors like Da Sica, Fellini, Bergman, Kurosawa. Studied film at University of Pennsylvania, MA at Annenberg School of Communicati
on, but disappointing. Job at Smith Klein for two years. Then returned to Britain [1964], two years with BBC directing documentari}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid7738219 es, but \lquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375 stuck in science\rquote . Ethos of filming, quality of film took priority over budget. Observed unhappiness of older producers. 
\par BBC boss refused his request to study part-time at LSE. Immediate boss unsympathetic when P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid7738219 eter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\langfenp1033\insrsid9441375\charrsid9441375 \rquote s mother died while he was in US. So left, although remained interested in film.
\par Took holiday from BBC in 1966, re-started reading anthropology. Met Raymond Firth who encouraged him to come to study at LSE. Offered SSRC scholarship. Went to visit Cyprus.
